catalogue, design, the ACI/.dlw badges, and presentation ONLY.

Dune is the creation of FRANK HERBERT (1920–1986), and the six-novel main corpus
(Dune 1965, Dune Messiah 1969, Children of Dune 1976, God Emperor of Dune 1981,
Heretics of Dune 1984, Chapterhouse: Dune 1985) is © the author's estate and his
publishers. This project is an UNOFFICIAL HOMAGE: a bibliography with original commentary
and ACI badge-work. NO copyrighted text from the novels is reproduced; quotation is
avoided in favour of original description.

By ROOT0's request, ONLY the six-novel Frank Herbert main corpus is catalogued; the later
prequels and sequels by Brian Herbert & Kevin J. Anderson are deliberately out of scope.

Character, place, and concept names (Paul Atreides, the Bene Gesserit, the spice melange,
the Kwisatz Haderach, Shai-Hulud, etc.) are the intellectual property of the Frank Herbert
estate, used here for identification and commentary under fair-use principles.

